[Keokuk is a city and a county seat of Lee County, Iowa, United States. It is also the most southerly city in Iowa.

The causative agent for hand-foot-and-mouth disease (HFMD) is an enterovirus. It is not the same as other diseases that have similar names: foot-and-mouth disease (sometimes called hoof-and-mouth disease). See previous ProMED post Hand, foot & mouth disease - USA (04): (CA) 20160505.4204778 for further discussion of HFMD. - Mod.LK


